CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 14, 1959, page A15 reads: "Surprise Party - The Matrons Council of Omega Grand Chapter, OES, gave a surprise, belated birthday party for Mrs. Esther Green, Grand Worthy Matron of the OES. Mrs. Mamie Smalls, president, presented a check to Mrs. Green (in front, center) as the following look on: Hazel Stovall, Mary Smith, Lula Miller, Willa Mae Wright, Sarah Ogden, Ada Freeman, Wayman Frazier, Luther Rice and Frederick Stanford. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of the Matrons Council of the Omega Grand Chapter, eight women, including Hazel Stovall, Mary Smith, Mamie Smalls presenting check to Esther Green, Lula Miller, Willa Mae Wright, Sarah Ogden, and Ada Freeman, and three men, including Wayman Frazier, Luther Rice, and Frederick Stanford, standing behind table covered with desserts and crepe paper turkey, in interior with cruet and vase patterned curtains, another version
